<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
The type-specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Michael, 1898" authorityName="Michael" authorityYear="1898" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoploderma" genus.bestMatchDistance="48" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cucullatum">H. cucullatum Ewing</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Michael, 1898" authorityName="Michael" authorityYear="1898" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoploderma" genus.bestMatchDistance="36" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="licnophorum">H. licnophorum Berlese</taxonomicName>
both have been collected by Crosby at the same locality: Columbia, Missouri. The original descriptions point to the same species, and Jacot (1933) regarded 
<taxonomicName authority="Michael, 1898" authorityName="Michael" authorityYear="1898" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoploderma" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cucullatum">cucullatum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Michael, 1898" authorityName="Michael" authorityYear="1898" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoploderma" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="licnophorum">licnophorum</taxonomicName>
already as Synonyms. Apparently Berlese himself also discovered this fact, because in 1923 he described a variety of &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cucullatus" subGenus="Hoplophorella">Phthiracarus (Hoplophorella) cucullatus</taxonomicName>
&quot;, of which the type-material is still labelled as &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="licnophora" subGenus="Hoplophorella" variety="obsoletior">Phthiracarus (Hoplophorella) licnophora var. obsoletior</taxonomicName>
&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
The type-slide (no. 142/5) of the species is still present in the Berlese Collection. There is no doubt about its identity with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoplophorella" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cucullata">cucullata</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
